{"meta":{"schema":"earth.healthscore.v1","methodologyVersion":"0.5","generatedAt":"1970-01-01T00:00:00.000Z","label":"Experimental Earth Health Score","disclosure":"Educational estimate only — NOT a scientific index. A coverage-weighted average of environmental DOMAINS, each scored 0–100 (higher = healthier): air (PM2.5 + NO2; US AQI a fallback), land cover (forest cover + canopy vitality), ocean warming (sea-surface temperature anomaly), ocean acidification (surface aragonite saturation), wildfire, glaciers, biodiversity, and protected-area conservation. v0.4 begins grounding the score in the PLANETARY BOUNDARIES framework (Richardson et al. 2023; Steffen et al. 2015; Planetary Health Check 2025): land cover (land-system change), air (atmospheric aerosol loading), and the NEW ocean-acidification domain are now scored as distance from a scientific boundary — 100 inside the safe operating space, falling to 0 at the high-risk threshold — instead of an ad-hoc scale. Ocean acidification is the latest (2025) boundary transgressed; the v0.3 ocean domain is split into ocean WARMING and ocean ACIDIFICATION (0.10 each of the former 0.20). Wildfire and glaciers are kept as CONTEXTUAL PROXIES, not boundary control variables. v0.5 marks ocean warming and acidification NOT-APPLICABLE for a continental-interior region whose centroid lies farther than 1500 km from open ocean — mirroring how glaciers are excluded where none lie within range — so a landlocked region's score reflects its land, while the population-exposure-weighted Global ring still counts ocean fully. Domain weights total 1.08 and renormalize by coverage, so missing data lowers confidence rather than the score; the Global number is population-exposure-weighted. Sensitivity: the boundary thresholds and the 0.10/0.10 ocean split are hand-set proposals pending owner ratification — the regrounded normalizers move the headline by a few points, and a ±0.05 change to any single domain weight shifts it by roughly a point or two. Representative pattern — not current conditions.","isLive":false,"weights":{"land-cover":0.25,"ocean":0.1,"ocean-acidification":0.1,"fire":0.2,"air":0.15,"cryosphere":0.1,"biodiversity":0.1,"conservation":0.08},"domainBasis":{"land-cover":"boundary","air":"boundary","ocean-acidification":"boundary","ocean":"boundary","biodiversity":"boundary","fire":"contextual-proxy","cryosphere":"contextual-proxy","conservation":"contextual-proxy"},"globalWeighting":"population-exposure","trendBasis":"cryosphere"},"global":{"score":48.9,"trend":"worsening","confidence":0.99,"subScores":[{"layerId":"air","normalized":62,"direction":"burden","weight":0.15},{"layerId":"land-cover","normalized":26.5,"direction":"benefit","weight":0.25},{"layerId":"ocean","normalized":52.5,"direction":"burden","weight":0.1},{"layerId":"ocean-acidification","normalized":91.8,"direction":"benefit","weight":0.1},{"layerId":"fire","normalized":67.3,"direction":"burden","weight":0.2},{"layerId":"biodiversity","normalized":51.2,"direction":"benefit","weight":0.1},{"layerId":"cryosphere","normalized":32.7,"direction":"burden","weight":0.1},{"layerId":"conservation","normalized":53.6,"direction":"benefit","weight":0.08}],"aiedsFactor":{"estimatedCo2eGrams":null,"window":"30d","scope":"device","blendedIntoScore":false,"note":"App AI digital footprint (AIEDS) — a SEPARATE chip the client fills from the local device; never blended into the planetary score."}},"regions":{"global":{"label":"Global","score":55.7,"trend":"worsening","confidence":1,"exposure":48,"subScores":[{"layerId":"air","normalized":75.8,"direction":"burden","weight":0.15},{"layerId":"land-cover","normalized":28.4,"direction":"benefit","weight":0.25},{"layerId":"ocean","normalized":50,"direction":"burden","weight":0.1},{"layerId":"ocean-acidification","normalized":100,"direction":"benefit","weight":0.1},{"layerId":"fire","normalized":72,"direction":"burden","weight":0.2},{"layerId":"biodiversity","normalized":52,"direction":"benefit","weigh